## Submission

Submit a single header file named `{{ artifact_name }}.hpp`.

Your header must:
- Declare the full `{{ artifact_name | capitalize }}` class interface
- Be self-contained (bring in your own `#include` directives)
- Compile cleanly at `-std=c++17`

## Grading

| Component             | Points |
|----------------------|--------|
| Compilation           | 10     |
| Correctness           | varies |
| Compile-Time Rules    | varies |

The grader checks not just whether your code runs correctly, but also that
your class properly **rejects** illegal operations at compile time (e.g.
mutating a `const` object, calling a deleted constructor, etc.).

Code that compiles when it should not, or fails to compile when it should,
will lose points.
